/**
 * HOMEPAGE SCENE (HomepageScene.jsx)
 * 
 * BEFORE: Generic sci-fi aesthetic with colourful floating orbs
 * AFTER: Academic research visualization with knowledge networks
 * 
 * Key Changes:
 * ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * 
 * 1. FLOATING ORBS → KNOWLEDGE CONSTELLATIONS
 *    Replaced glowing spheres with pulsing nodes connected by subtle lines.
 *    This creates a "research network" feeling rather than "gaming dashboard".
 *    
 *    Visual Effect:
 *    • Nodes pulse in sync with citation/collaboration metaphor
 *    • Connections fade in/out to suggest dynamic relationships
 *    • Positioned as a knowledge web, not arbitrary orbs
 * 
 * 2. SINGLE PARTICLE FIELD → LAYERED STARFIELD SYSTEM
 *    Created 3-layer particle system:
 *    
 *    Layer 1 (Background): 2500 tiny particles
 *    • Smallest particles (0.01–0.12 size)
 *    • Lowest opacity (0.25)
 *    • Creates deep-field astronomical effect
 *    
 *    Layer 2 (Research): 300 medium particles in orbital rings
 *    • Rotating around center (citation orbit metaphor)
 *    • Higher opacity (0.15–0.4)
 *    • Suggests active research areas
 *    
 *    Layer 3 (Knowledge): Constellation nodes (6–8 nodes)
 *    • Largest, brightest elements
 *    • Pulsing with research activity
 *    • Connected by citation lines
 *    
 *    Performance: Still efficient (~2800 total particles)
 * 
 * 3. WORDMARK: ADDED ANIMATED "ACADEME" TYPOGRAPHY
 *    • IBM Plex Sans for scholarly sans-serif feel
 *    • Large, readable, centered
 *    • Glowing underline suggests illuminated knowledge
 *    • Subtle rotation and breathing animation
 *    • Acts as anchor point for entire scene
 * 
 * 4. GRID PLANE → RESEARCH BLUEPRINT GRID
 *    • Renamed from "GridPlane" to "AcademicGrid"
 *    • Added perspective rotation: rotate={[-Math.PI / 2.4, 0, 0]}
 *    • Reduced opacity for subtlety
 *    • Feels like scientific plotting paper, not gaming grid
 * 
 * 5. COLOUR SCHEME
 *    OLD: #6366f1, #7c3aed, #06b6d4, #10b981 (mixed rainbow)
 *    NEW: Single unified palette using only #4F6BFF (primary) and #7DA8FF (secondary)
 *    
 *    Why? Academic publications use restrained color palettes.
 *    This feels "published" not "styled".
 * 
 * 6. LIGHTING & ATMOSPHERE
 *    • Reduced particle opacity for scholarly restraint
 *    • Added foggy rendering to suggest research depth
 *    • Blending changed from NormalBlending to AdditiveBlending for glow
 *    • Color temperature: cool/academic (not warm/friendly)
 */

