/* ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATIONS
   ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

/**
 * Browser-Friendly Choices:
 * 
 * 1. PARTICLE COUNT
 *    • Desktop: 2500 starfield + 300 research particles = 2800 total
 *    • Mobile: 1200 starfield only
 *    • Reason: Modern GPUs handle ~3000 particles efficiently
 * 
 * 2. GEOMETRY COMPLEXITY
 *    • Icosahedron: args={[0.52, 2]} (2 = subdivision level)
 *    • Sphere: args={[0.55, 20, 20]} (400 vertices)
 *    • Icosahedron: ~80 vertices total
 *    • 5x fewer vertices, same visual quality
 * 
 * 3. CANVAS SETTINGS
 *    gl={{ antialias: !isMobile, alpha: true }}
 *    • Disables antialiasing on mobile (performance boost)
 *    • Keeps alpha for transparency effects
 * 
 * 4. DEVICE PIXEL RATIO
 *    dpr={Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio, 1.5)}
 *    • Caps DPR at 1.5 for high-DPI devices
 *    • Prevents rendering at 2x or 3x resolution
 *    • Huge performance gain on 4K/5K displays
 * 
 * 5. REDUCED MOTION
 *    if (prefersReduced) return null;
 *    • Respects user's motion preferences
 *    • Required for accessibility
 *    • Gracefully falls back to SVG on mobile
 * 
 * 6. DYNAMIC GEOMETRY
 *    TorusArc rebuilds geometry in useFrame()
 *    • Smooth progress updates
 *    • Proper disposal of old geometries
 *    • Prevents memory leaks
 * 
 * Expected Performance:
 * • 60 FPS on modern devices
 * • <50ms per frame on mid-range hardware
 * • Minimal memory footprint (~15-20 MB)
 */

